HEADWORD: Gril
<hw>Gril</hw> <pr>(gr⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>gril</ets> harsh; akin to G. <ets>grell</ets> offending the ear or
eye, shrill, dazzling, MHG. <ets>grel</ets> angry; cf. AS.
<ets>gallan</ets> to provoke.]</ety> <def>Harsh; hard; severe; stern;
rough.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Rom. of R.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

